<h2>What Is Aircraft Tyre Shelf Life?</h2>

<p>
Aircraft tyre shelf life refers to the maximum recommended storage period
before a tyre is mounted and placed into service. Manufacturers typically
define limits based on rubber compound composition and environmental
storage conditions.
</p>

<p>
Proper storage in controlled humidity and temperature environments is
critical to preserving structural integrity.
</p>

<h2>Safety Risks of Expired Tyres</h2>

<ul>
<li>Sidewall cracking due to rubber degradation</li>
<li>Reduced structural integrity under landing load</li>
<li>Tread separation risk</li>
<li>Increased blowout probability</li>
</ul>

